    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>apple[s]</strong> into wedges, remove the core, and finely slice the wedges</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-desserts-with-salted-caramel-apple-galette/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced apple</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>agave </strong>and most of your <strong>ground cinnamon</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until well coated \u2013 this is your <strong>cinnamon apple</strong></p><p>Cover with cling film, pierce a few hole sin top and put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 3-4 min or until softened, then set aside to cool with the cling film removed</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-desserts-with-salted-caramel-apple-galette/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rolled pastry</strong> to the tray[s] and prick it all over with a fork (this will stop it getting a soggy bottom!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-desserts-with-salted-caramel-apple-galette/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Discard the liquid from the cooked apple</p><p>Top the <strong>pastry</strong> with the <strong>cinnamon apple</strong>, leaving a 2cm border around the edges</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-desserts-with-salted-caramel-apple-galette/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fold the <strong>pastry border</strong> over the edge of the filling</p><p>Tip: Start from one corner and work around in one direction, overlapping the pastry each time</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You will need to make multiple galettes!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 18-20 min or until the pastry is golden, cooked through and the edges have puffed up \u2013 this is your<strong> apple galette</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-desserts-with-salted-caramel-apple-galette/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> (save the rest for later!) to a heatproof jug with a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>brown</strong> <strong>sugar </strong>and stir together</p><p>Tip: Don't have brown sugar? Use white sugar instead!</p><p>Put the jug in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 1 min or until melted, then stir until combined</p><p>Add your <strong>smoked sea salt flakes</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then leave to cool slightly \u2013 this is your <strong>salted caramel sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-desserts-with-salted-caramel-apple-galette/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>pecans </strong>in their bag with a<strong> rolling pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p><p>Top your <strong>galette[s]</strong> with the <strong>crushed pecans</strong> and return to the oven for a final 2-3 min or until the nuts are lightly golden, the apple is tender and the pastry cooked through and golden</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>remaining cinnamon </strong>and your <strong>maple syrup</strong> and stir together until just combined \u2013 this is your <strong>maple cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-desserts-with-salted-caramel-apple-galette/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice and serve the <strong>apple galette</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the <strong>salted caramel sauce</strong></p><p>Dollop the <strong>maple cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
